Currently when enabling and disabling debug in the logs you get:

{noformat}
2009-07-09 12:00:01,432 INFO  [btpool0-6] fisheye.app EditServerSettingsAction-toggleDebug - Turning ON DEBUG, log level was ERROR but will now be set to INFO
2009-07-09 12:01:36,515 INFO  [btpool0-7] fisheye.app EditServerSettingsAction-toggleDebug - Disabling DEBUG, log level was INFO but will now be set to WARN
{noformat}

Although what is actually happening is when you turn on DEBUG, the log level is set to DEBUG from WARN and when you turn it off it is set to WARN from DEBUG, but the above confusing messages are printed.

Once we have integrated with web proxy, we can't remove the *Proxy port* from the Admin page. (_FishEye and Crucible >  Admin > Server Settings_). 

A workaround is shutdown the server, then manually remove it from the _config.xml_ file: 
For example;
*Change From*
{noformat}
<http bind=":8060" proxy-port="80" proxy-host="localhost"/>
{noformat}
*To*
{noformat}
<http bind=":8060" />
{noformat}
and then restart the server.

Besides, says the web server is down, we can't direct access to the default Fisheye port e.g http://localhost:8060/fisheye.

Once you have removed a repository in Fisheye, all the caches, indexes and temporarily files still retain in;
* {{<FISHEYE_INST>\var\cache\REPONAME}}
* {{<FISHEYE_INST>\var\tmp\REPONAME}}
* {{<FISHEYE_INST>\var\data\DiffTextCache\REPONAME}}

A workaround is to remove those files manually. To do so,
# Delete the following directories
* {{<FISHEYE_INST>\var\cache\REPONAME}}
* {{<FISHEYE_INST>\var\tmp\REPONAME}}
* {{<FISHEYE_INST>\var\data\DiffTextCache\REPONAME}}

where REPONAME is the NAME of the repository that was deleted. (You do not need to stop fisheye, just ensure you have stopped and deleted the repository from the UI before deleting the above directories).
